{"id":8579,"date":"2025-09-22T11:02:12","date_gmt":"2025-09-22T11:02:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=8579"},"modified":"2025-12-04T11:48:52","modified_gmt":"2025-12-04T11:48:52","slug":"kedarkantha","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/kedarkantha\/","title":{"rendered":"KEDARKANTHA"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8835,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[104],"activities":[],"trip_types":[75],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[77],"class_list":["post-8579","trip","type-trip","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","destination-special-adventure-tours","trip_types-customized-domestic-tour","tripcategory-customized-domestic-tour"],"packages_ids":[8580],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-8579","price":12777,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":6,"nights":5,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Embark on one of India\u2019s most popular Himalayan treks with the <strong>Kedarkantha Adventure Tour<\/strong>, a journey that blends thrill, natural beauty, and a sense of achievement. Nestled in Uttarakhand\u2019s Govind Pashu Vihar National Park, Kedarkantha is renowned for its <strong>snow-clad trails, dense pine forests, and breathtaking 360\u00b0 summit views<\/strong> of Himalayan peaks like Swargarohini, Bandarpoonch, and Black Peak. The trek is ideal for both beginners and seasoned trekkers, offering a moderate level of challenge with rewarding vistas at every step. Camp under starry skies, enjoy the crisp mountain air, and experience the magic of the Himalayas in winter. With professional trek leaders, safety measures, and all essentials arranged, the Kedarkantha trek is the perfect adventure to ignite your spirit of exploration.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":" 3 star premium hotel stay\n All transfers and sightseeing by AC Vehicle\n Breakfast, Dinner, Lunch\n Toll Tax\n Parking\n Driver Allowance\nTravel Goodies\n 24 x 7 On tour Assistance\n All cost from EX Destination","cost_excludes":" Any meals other than those mentioned above in inclusions\n Airfare \/ Train Ticket\n GST 5%\n All monument entry Fees\n Any portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all items of personal nature\n Any services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions\nEntrance fees to Monuments & other sightseeing points\nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle malfunctions, political disturbances, etc.\nAnything not mentioned in inclusions","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1. What is the difficulty level of the Kedarkantha trek? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The trek is considered easy to moderate, making it suitable for beginners with basic fitness as well as experienced trekkers.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2. How many days does the Kedarkantha trek take? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The trek usually takes 5 to 6 days, including travel, acclimatization, and the summit climb.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3. What is the best time to do the Kedarkantha trek? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The trek is most popular in winter (December to April) when the trails are snow-covered, offering stunning views.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"